snippet.title: Putin Says Ukrainian F-16s Will be Destroyed Just Like NATO Tanks | From The Frontline
snippet.description:
Putin Says Ukrainian F-16s Will be Destroyed Just Like NATO Tanks | From The Frontline

The F-16 Fighting Falcon completed 50 years in military service in July. It was made by the United States in 1974 and has been flown by over 30 nations with at least 3,000 aircraft in Service. Even after all these years, the aircraft remains in high demand as Turkey, Argentina and Taiwan continue to buy these jets. The most recent member of the F-16 Viper group is Ukraine. Zelensky received the jets on the 4th of August. A special ceremony was held to induct the jets into the Ukrainian Air Force. However, Russian President Vladimir Putin says that the Ukrainian F-16s will be shot down just like the NATO leopard and Abrams tanks were destroyed in the battlefield. To know more, watch the full video.

snippet.description:

Bangladesh Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has stepped down and has fled the country after the army reportedly gave a 45-minute ultimatum. snippet.title: What Does Sheikh Hasina’s Departure Mean for India? | Firstpost PoV
snippet.description:
What Does Sheikh Hasina’s Departure Mean for India? | Firstpost PoV

Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has resigned and fled the country ending a 15-year rule of the South Asian Nation. Hasina’s exit comes after weeks of deadly anti-government protests which saw one of the deadliest days of demonstrations on the 4th of August. Hasina had given “shoot-at-sight” orders to the army which resulted in the death of over 300 protesters since July. Now, the Bangladeshi army will form an interim government as Hasina reportedly heads to London via India. What does this mean for India and the region? Is New Delhi staring at border and security crisis with Hasina Gone? To get more insight into the issue, Firstpost spoke to Ambassador Bhaswati Mukherjee, former Indian diplomat and author of book Bengal and it's Partition: An untold story.

snippet.description:

Dolce & Gabbana, the renowned Italian luxury brand, has launched a new product: a perfume called "Fefe" exclusively for dogs. Priced at around $100, the alcohol-free body mist is packaged in a chic glass bottle adorned with a gold-plated paw print and comes with a designer dog collar. The fragrance features notes of ylang-ylang, musk, and sandalwood, offering a delicate scent for pampered pooches. While some may question the need for canine perfumes, the luxury pet market is booming, with consumers increasingly willing to splurge on their furry companions. This latest offering from Dolce & Gabbana underscores the growing trend of high-end products for pets.

snippet.title: Are Hippopotamus Capable of Flying? | Beyond Bizarre
snippet.description:
Are Hippopotamus Capable of Flying? | Beyond Bizarre

British scientists have made a surprising discovery: hippopotamuses can achieve brief moments of lift-off when they reach top speeds, challenging the conventional notion that these massive animals are strictly terrestrial. Typically associated with their large size and aquatic lifestyle, hippos were observed to get all four feet off the ground about fifteen percent of the time during high-speed chases. This revelation, based on meticulous analysis of footage, shows that hippos, despite their weight, can exhibit unexpected agility. The study highlights the challenges of observing these nocturnal and dangerous creatures, offering a fresh perspective on the capabilities of one of Africa's most iconic animals.

snippet.title: Fast and Factual LIVE: At Least 10 Dead in Russian Missile Attack on Ukrainian Supermarket
snippet.description:
Fast and Factual LIVE: At Least 10 Dead in Russian Missile Attack on Ukrainian Supermarket

A Russian missile strike targeted a supermarket in the Ukrainian town of Kostiantynivka, located in the front-line Donetsk region, on August 9. The strike has led to the deaths of at least ten people and injured 35 others, according to Ukrainian officials. Images and videos shared by officials show heavy black smoke billowing from the damaged building. President Volodymyr Zelensky stated on X that "Russian terrorists hit an ordinary supermarket and a post office," adding that there are still people trapped under the rubble.

snippet.title: Pakistan: Record-Breaking Rain Floods Streets Of Lahore, At Least Three Killed | Firstpost Earth
snippet.description:
Pakistan: Record-Breaking Rain Floods Streets Of Lahore, At Least Three Killed | Firstpost Earth  

Pakistan’s cultural city of Lahore experienced record-breaking rainfall on Thursday resulting in at least three fatalities. The heavy rain inundated streets, disrupted traffic and impacted daily life. The downpour began before dawn and is anticipated to continue intermittently for a week, as per Pakistani authorities. They warned that the rains could trigger flash floods and landslides. The intensity of the rainfall led to widespread flooding, with rainwater seeping into wards of hospitals. Some areas recorded an unprecedented 353 millimetres of rain within three hours, surpassing the previous 44-year record set in July 1980, which was 332 millimetres over the same period. Meanwhile, the death toll from rain-related incidents in the past month has exceeded 100.

---

snippet.title: Mumbai Rain: Orange Alert Issued, Flight and Railway Operations Disrupted | Firstpost Earth
snippet.description:
Mumbai Rain: Orange Alert Issued, Flight and Railway Operations Disrupted | Firstpost Earth  

India’s financial capital, Mumbai, is grappling with extensive rainfall. The Indian weather bureau, the Indian Meteorological Department (IMD), has put the city on orange alert, with local police officials advising people to stay indoors. All schools and colleges in the city have declared a holiday in light of the weather. Flight and train services have also faced significant disruptions. Central Railways officials said “loco pilots decreased speed” due to low visibility and airlines asked passengers to check the flight status before heading to the airport.

snippet.title: LIVE: Russia Bombs Ukraine, As Ukrainian Troops Fight in Russia's Kursk | Vantage with Palki Sharma
snippet.description:
LIVE: Russia Bombs Ukraine, As Ukrainian Troops Fight in Russia's Kursk | Vantage with Palki Sharma

Russia bombed a supermarket in eastern Ukraine today (August 9), killing at least 10 people and injuring 35 others. The bombing comes after a surprise attack from the Ukrainian army earlier this week, which appeared to be the most significant assault on Russian soil since Moscow invaded Kyiv in February 2022. In their boldest operation yet, the Ukrainian forces entered Kursk region on Tuesday with reportedly 1,000 troops, armed with Western armoured vehicles, artillery, and drones. They also released footage claiming that Russian forces are surrendering to the Ukrainian troops. After this incursion, Russian President Vladimir Putin declared a state of emergency in Kursk and announced the deployment of additional troops and munitions to the region. On Vantage tonight, Palki Sharma brings you the full story.

snippet.title: LIVE: Iran & Hezbollah Divided Over Response Against Israel? | Vantage with Palki Sharma
snippet.description:
LIVE: Iran & Hezbollah Divided Over Response Against Israel? | Vantage with Palki Sharma

West Asia has been gripped by fears of a wider war as Iran mulls its response to Israel. This comes after Hamas Chief Ismail Haniyeh was killed in a strike in Iran's capital Tehran a few days back. Iran has blamed Israel for the attack; however, Israel has not claimed responsibility for the strike. Iran has vowed to retaliate against Israel. The global community has different reactions to Iran's imminent retaliatory attack on Israel. Recently, the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) released a joint statement condemning Israel for Hamas Chief Haniyeh's killing in Tehran.  While Russia is arming Tehran with weapons, the Western nations want Iran to exercise restraint.

 One of the Israel's closest allies, the US is moving more and more assets to West Asia as the threat of a wider war looms over the region. While Iran is still planning its response against Israel, Iranian proxy groups like Hezbollah in Lebanon and the Houthis in Yemen are seemingly running out of patience. Hezbollah chief Hassan Nasrallah recently said that the group may attack Israel alone. On Vantage tonight, Palki Sharma tells you more.

localized.description:
LIVE: Iran & Hezbollah Divided Over Response Against Israel? | Vantage with Palki Sharma

West Asia has been gripped by fears of a wider war as Iran mulls its response to Israel. This comes after Hamas Chief Ismail Haniyeh was killed in a strike in Iran's capital Tehran a few days back. Iran has blamed Israel for the attack; however, Israel has not claimed responsibility for the strike. Iran has vowed to retaliate against Israel. The global community has different reactions to Iran's imminent retaliatory attack on Israel. Recently, the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) released a joint statement condemning Israel for Hamas Chief Haniyeh's killing in Tehran.  While Russia is arming Tehran with weapons, the Western nations want Iran to exercise restraint.

 One of the Israel's closest allies, the US is moving more and more assets to West Asia as the threat of a wider war looms over the region. While Iran is still planning its response against Israel, Iranian proxy groups like Hezbollah in Lebanon and the Houthis in Yemen are seemingly running out of patience. Hezbollah chief Hassan Nasrallah recently said that the group may attack Israel alone. On Vantage tonight, Palki Sharma tells you more.

snippet.title: Scientist Lives in Underwater Bunker, De-ages by 10 Years | Vantage with Palki Sharma
snippet.description:
Scientist Lives in Underwater Bunker, De-ages by 10 Years | Vantage with Palki Sharma

Scientist Joseph Dituri spent a record-breaking 100 days underwater. When he emerged, his age had reversed by 10 years. Before the mission, 55-year-old Dituri’s biological age was 44. But his biological age reduced to 34 after he emerged out of the water. The diver lived in a bunker under the Atlantic Ocean as part of NASA study. He was living in a highly pressurised environment. High pressure can reverse the body's age down to the cellular level. So Dituri's health underwent remarkable transformation during the underwater mission. How did it happen? Is it possible to reverse age without living in an underwater bunker? Palki Sharma brings you the report.

---

snippet.description:
Indonesia Volcanic Eruptions: Why is Cold Lava Deadly? | Vantage with Palki Sharma

Indonesia’s second most active volcano sent ash 4 km into the sky, with purple lightning flashing around its crater. Thousands evacuated from the nearby villages as rescue teams moved people to emergency shelters. As residents evacuate and rescue teams mobilize, the danger of cold lava flows looms large. Indonesia, with its 127 active volcanoes, sits on the Pacific Ring of Fire, making volcanic eruptions a constant threat. With over 21,000 eruptions last year, Indonesia is no stranger to volcanic disasters. But can it do better? Can disaster preparedness help save lives? Palki Sharma tells you.

snippet.title: LIVE: India-China Border Conflict | Ruto Dismisses Cabinet | Vantage this week with Palki Sharma
snippet.description:
LIVE: India-China Border Conflict | Ruto Dismisses Cabinet | Vantage this week with Palki Sharma

A report claims India plans to construct 12 hydropower stations in Arunachal Pradesh. This project is expected to cost a billion dollars. India's Finance Minister, Nirmala Sitharaman could announce the new project in Budget speech on July 23. The new hydropower stations will be built to bridge the gap between supply and demand for power. This new project will also help in the development of India's north-eastern state. But today, China has opposed the plan. In an official statement, China said, "South Tibet is China's territory". China has termed the Indian state Arunachal Pradesh as 'South Tibet'. In recent years, China has stepped up its claims on the Indian state - which have no basis in history or backing of the international community.

snippet.title: China Tells its Nationals to "Online Shame" Taiwanese Officials | Firstpost America
snippet.description:
China Tells its Nationals to "Online Shame" Taiwanese Officials | Firstpost America

China has escalated its campaign against Taiwan by launching new webpages that target top Taiwanese officials, labelling them as "diehard secessionists." These pages urge the public to report any information on these individuals, aiming to increase pressure on the island’s leadership. Among those listed are Taiwan’s Vice-President and key security officials, all advocates for the island’s independence. This move marks a significant escalation in Beijing’s efforts to assert control over Taiwan, which it views as a breakaway province. Taiwan’s government has firmly rejected these tactics, insisting that Chinese laws have no jurisdiction over the island.

snippet.title: UK Violence News LIVE: Petrol Bombs Thrown at Police During Clashes in Londonderry
snippet.description:
UK Violence News LIVE: Petrol Bombs Thrown at Police During Clashes in Londonderry

Anti-racism protests continue to escalate in the United Kingdom. Ten police officers have been injured and one person arrested during disorder in Londonderry, the Police Service of Northern Ireland (PSNI) has said. Petrol bombs, fireworks and stones were thrown by nationalist youths at police lines during trouble in Nailors Row on Saturday evening. Reportedly, British Prime Minister Keir Starmer has cancelled a planned holiday to focus on his government's response to a series of racist riots that targeted Muslims and migrants. Thousands of police officers remained on duty over the weekend in case violence flared again although for a fourth day in a row on Saturday counter-protesters far outnumbered anti-migration demonstrators in several towns and cities.

snippet.title: WATCH | US Elections 2024: Kamala Harris Says She Supports Eliminating Taxes on Tips, Like Trump
snippet.description:
WATCH | US Elections 2024: Kamala Harris Says She Supports Eliminating Taxes on Tips, Like Trump

US Vice President Kamala Harris told supporters in Nevada on Saturday she supported eliminating taxes on tips, taking a similar position to her rival Donald Trump in an effort to win over service workers, an important constituency in the state. Harris and her Democratic running mate, Minnesota Governor Tim Walz, wrapped up a multi-day tour of battleground states on Saturday with their stop in Nevada, a western state that could play a pivotal role in the November 5 presidential election. "It is my promise to everyone here when I am president we will continue to fight for working families, including to raise the minimum wage and eliminate taxes on tips for service and hospitality workers," Harris said.

snippet.title: WATCH | US Elections 2024: Trump Attacks Kamala Harris and Her Running Mate Walz at Bozeman Rally
snippet.description:
WATCH | US Elections 2024: Trump Attacks Kamala Harris and Her Running Mate Walz at Bozeman Rally

Former US President Donald Trump held a rally in Bozeman, Montana, on Friday (August 9), a state that Republicans have carried in every presidential race since 1996. The scene at the rally was charged with energy, as thousands of Trump supporters waved flags, wearing red "Make America Great Again" hats, and shouting slogans in unison. The former president's remarks were interspersed with applause and standing ovations as he reiterated his commitment to "protecting American values" and reversing the policies of the current administration. Trump again attacked Harris in personal terms and criticised her for not doing interviews or major press conferences since she became the Democratic candidate.

snippet.title: Russia Ukraine War News LIVE: Zelensky Acknowledges Ukraine's Military Operation in Russia
snippet.description:
Russia Ukraine War News LIVE: Zelensky Acknowledges Ukraine's Military Operation in Russia

Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky acknowledged for the first time on Saturday that Ukrainian forces were fighting in the surprise offensive in Russia's Kursk, as attacks on the border region continued with authorities rushing to evacuate people. Moscow's forces were in their sixth day of intense battles against Kyiv's largest incursion into Russian territory since the start of the war, which left southwestern parts of Russia vulnerable before reinforcement started arriving. In a sign of the gravity of the situation, Russia imposed a sweeping security regime in three border regions on Saturday, while Belarus, a staunch ally of Moscow, sent more troops to its border with Ukraine, accusing Kyiv of violating its air space.

snippet.title: Vinesh Phogat News| "She Deserves The Silver": Sourav Ganguly On Vinesh Phogat's Appeal For Medal
snippet.description:
Former India skipper Sourav Ganguly opened up on Vinesh Phogat's disqualification from the final of women's 50 kg wrestling at the Paris Olympics and said that she deserves the silver medal. Following her disqualification from the Paris Olympics final, Phogat announced her retirement from wrestling on Thursday. Phogat had advanced to the gold medal bout by defeating Cuba's Yusneylis Guzman Lopez 5-0 in the semi-finals on Tuesday night. She was set to compete against the United States' Sarah Ann Hildebrandt for the gold medal but was disqualified on Wednesday for breaching the weight limit. After her disqualification, Phogat requested the CAS to award her the silver medal. Speaking to the reporters, Ganguly said that he doesn't know the exact rules but she "must have qualified properly".

localized.title: Vinesh Phogat News| "She Deserves The Silver": Sourav Ganguly On Vinesh Phogat's Appeal For Medal
localized.description:
Former India skipper Sourav Ganguly opened up on Vinesh Phogat's disqualification from the final of women's 50 kg wrestling at the Paris Olympics and said that she deserves the silver medal. Following her disqualification from the Paris Olympics final, Phogat announced her retirement from wrestling on Thursday. Phogat had advanced to the gold medal bout by defeating Cuba's Yusneylis Guzman Lopez 5-0 in the semi-finals on Tuesday night. She was set to compete against the United States' Sarah Ann Hildebrandt for the gold medal but was disqualified on Wednesday for breaching the weight limit. After her disqualification, Phogat requested the CAS to award her the silver medal. Speaking to the reporters, Ganguly said that he doesn't know the exact rules but she "must have qualified properly".

snippet.title: Paris Olympics 2024 | The Firsts, Near Misses: India End Paris Olympics Campaign With 6 Medals
snippet.description:
India's Paris Olympics campaign concluded as Reetika Hooda fell short in the wrestling quarterfinals, and golfers Aditi Ashok and Diksha Dagar finished out of medal contention. A total of 117 Indian athletes participated across 16 sports at the Paris Games: archery, athletics, badminton, boxing, equestrian, golf, hockey, judo, rowing, sailing, shooting, swimming, wrestling, table tennis, and tennis. India clinched six medals at the Paris Olympics, one silver and five bronze. Although hopes were high for a historic performance, the country fell just short of surpassing its previous best at the rescheduled Tokyo Olympics in 2021, when they secured seven medals (1 gold, 2 silver, and 4 bronze.) and ranked 48th.

snippet.title: Nepal Plane Crash: Relatives Of Plane Crash Victims Mourn Over The Demise Of Loved Ones
snippet.description:
Eighteen people were killed when a small passenger plane belonging to Nepal's Saurya Airlines crashed and caught fire while taking off from the capital Kathmandu on July 24.  Relatives and loved ones of victims mourned outside the Tribhuvan University Institute of Medicine, where a post-mortem of the bodies was due to take place. The plane, carrying two crew members and 17 technicians, was going for regular maintenance to Nepal's new Pokhara airport, which opened in January last year and is equipped with aircraft maintenance hangars, they said.
According to Tej Bahadur Poudyal, the spokesman for Kathmandu's Tribhuvan International Airport, the captain was the only person on board to have survived the crash, and is receiving treatment at hospital.

snippet.title: Kolkata Doctor Murder Case | Kolkata Trainee Doctor Was Sexually Assaulted Before Murder: Police
snippet.description:
The post-mortem of the woman trainee doctor, who was found dead at a state-run hospital in Kolkata on Friday, has confirmed that she was sexually assaulted before being murdered, a senior police official said today. 

The second-year post-graduate medical student reportedly had a late dinner on Thursday after which she went to study in the seminar hall on the third floor of the RG Kar Medical College and Hospital. The 31-year-old was seen in an unconscious state the next morning.

snippet.title: Microsoft Crashed | Airports Clearing Backlog After Global IT Chaos, Centre Shares An Update
snippet.description:
Airports across India are still grappling with issues from yesterday's massive Microsoft outage. Although the situation has improved significantly since Friday's chaotic scenes, passengers continue to face challenges, particularly at Delhi's Indira Gandhi International Airport (IGI).

At Delhi's IGI Airport's Terminal 3, passengers experienced some improvement today, but a few problems persist. Yesterday, the automatic self-drop baggage and check-in machines were non-functional, causing long queues outside Gate No. 5 in Terminal 3. While many passengers can print out their boarding passes today, international travellers still face issues with boarding pass generation, with some being issued manual passes inside the airport.

snippet.title: PM Modi Leaves For Home After Completing Two-Country Visit
snippet.description:
Prime Minister Narendra Modi left for home on Wednesday after concluding his visit to Russia and Austria, during which he held talks with the top leadership of the two countries and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation. "PM @narendramodi emplanes for New Delhi after concluding a successful visit to Austria," the Prime Minister's Office said in a post on X.

During his visit, he told Russian President Putin that a solution to the Ukraine conflict is not possible on the battlefield, and peace talks do not succeed amidst bombs, guns and bullets. The prime minister was on Tuesday officially conferred the 'Order of St Andrew the Apostle' award by President Putin for his contribution to fostering bilateral ties between the two countries. The award was announced in 2019.From Moscow, PM Modi travelled to Austria, becoming the first Indian prime minister to visit the country in 41 years.During his visit, PM Modi met Austrian President Alexander Van der Bellen and Chancellor Karl Nehammer and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation in several sectors, including the environment and combating climate change.

He also discussed the ongoing disputes in the world, including the Ukraine conflict and the situation in West Asia, with the two leaders. "My visit to Austria has been historic and immensely productive. New vigour has been added to the friendship between our nations. I am glad to have attended diverse programmes while in Vienna. Gratitude to Chancellor @karlnehammer, the Austrian Government and people for their hospitality and affection," the prime minister said in a post on X. PM Modi first travelled to Russia, where he participated in the 22nd India-Russia summit with President Vladimir Putin, in his first trip to Moscow since the Ukraine conflict.

localized.title: PM Modi Leaves For Home After Completing Two-Country Visit
localized.description:
Prime Minister Narendra Modi left for home on Wednesday after concluding his visit to Russia and Austria, during which he held talks with the top leadership of the two countries and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation. "PM @narendramodi emplanes for New Delhi after concluding a successful visit to Austria," the Prime Minister's Office said in a post on X.

During his visit, he told Russian President Putin that a solution to the Ukraine conflict is not possible on the battlefield, and peace talks do not succeed amidst bombs, guns and bullets. The prime minister was on Tuesday officially conferred the 'Order of St Andrew the Apostle' award by President Putin for his contribution to fostering bilateral ties between the two countries. The award was announced in 2019.From Moscow, PM Modi travelled to Austria, becoming the first Indian prime minister to visit the country in 41 years.During his visit, PM Modi met Austrian President Alexander Van der Bellen and Chancellor Karl Nehammer and discussed ways to expand bilateral cooperation in several sectors, including the environment and combating climate change.

He also discussed the ongoing disputes in the world, including the Ukraine conflict and the situation in West Asia, with the two leaders. "My visit to Austria has been historic and immensely productive. New vigour has been added to the friendship between our nations. I am glad to have attended diverse programmes while in Vienna. Gratitude to Chancellor @karlnehammer, the Austrian Government and people for their hospitality and affection," the prime minister said in a post on X. PM Modi first travelled to Russia, where he participated in the 22nd India-Russia summit with President Vladimir Putin, in his first trip to Moscow since the Ukraine conflict.

snippet.title: Eric Garcetti's Message On India-US Ties After PM Modi's Russia Visit: "If We Take It For Granted.."
snippet.description:
US Ambassador to India, Eric Garcetti on July 11 talked about the relationship between United States and India. Addressing an event, he said, "It's important for us as Americans and as Indians to remember the more we put into this relationship, the more we will get out. The more we insist on a kind of cynical calculation in the place of a trusted relationship, the less we will get. As I also remind my Indian friends, while it is wider and it is deeper than it's ever been, it is not yet deep enough that if we take it for granted from the Indian side towards America, I'll fight a lot of defence battles trying to help this relationship ahead."

snippet.title: Bhole Baba On Hathras Tragedy | "Disturbed, But Who Can Avoid The Inevitable": 'Bhole Baba'
snippet.description:
Narayan Sakaar Hari alias Bhole Baba, in his first reaction to the Hathras stampede which killed 121 people on July 2, said that whoever has come to this Earth has to depart one day.
The self-styled godman also claimed that a conspiracy was hatched during the 'satsang' which led to the stampede at Hathras in Uttar Pradesh.

Speaking exclusively to IANS, Bhole Baba said, "We are very disturbed and distressed after the July 2 incident. But, who can avoid the inevitable? Whoever has come to this Earth will have to depart one day, although the timing may differ."

snippet.title: Rahul Gandhi News | Army Responds To Rahul Gandhi's Agniveer Claim | Biggest Stories Of July 3, 2024
snippet.description:
The Army, in a late-night post on Wednesday, has clarified that Agniveer Ajay Kumar's family has been paid ₹ 98.39 lakh within hours of Rahul Gandhi's claim that Rajnath Singh "lied" to parliament about compensation of ₹ 1 crore being paid to the family. 
"Certain posts on Social Media have brought out that compensation hasn't been paid to the Next of Kin of Agniveer Ajay Kumar who lost his life in the line of duty," said the Army in a post on X, underlining that it salutes the supreme sacrifice made by the Agniveer.

snippet.title: Atishi Latest News | "She Is Brave..." Akhilesh Yadav After Meeting Delhi Minister Atishi
snippet.description:
Delhi Water Crisis: Samajwadi Party chief Akhilesh Yadav arrived at Lok Nayak Hospital to meet Delhi Water Minister Atishi who was admitted here. Atishi was brought here on the late night of June 25 after her health deteriorated during her indefinite hunger strike over the Delhi water crisis and supply of water from Haryana.

Akhilesh Yadav said, “She is brave and knows how to fight... She has been fighting the people of Delhi... Since the BJP govt has been formed in the centre, the problems of the CMs have increased. The government is not providing the required assistance... They have done the most injustice to Arvind Kejriwal... The central govt is creating obstacles and harassing him... He has been trapped again in a fake case so that he does not come out.”

snippet.title: Delhi Water Crisis | AAP's Atishi In ICU After Blood Sugar Levels Drop, Ends Hunger Strike
snippet.description:
Delhi Minister Atishi's hunger strike over the water crisis in the national capital ended on Tuesday after her health deteriorated, her party said. Addressing a press conference, Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) MP Sanjay Singh said that the 43-year-old water minister was admitted to Delhi's Lok Nayak Hospital after her blood sugar level dropped to 36. "After her blood sugar levels dropped, doctors advised us that she should be immediately admitted to the hospital or she may lose her life," Mr Singh said.

snippet.title: Supreme Court On NEET 2024 | "Avoid Flip Flops": Top Court Raps Exam Body, Says Must Fix Loopholes
snippet.description:
The Supreme Court has directed the National Testing Agency - the under-fire central body responsible for the conduct of the NEET-UG test - to "rectify deficiencies in the exam system", including using technology to identify faults in its cybersecurity profile to prevent paper leaks. The court also told the NTA to avoid "flip-flops" in the context of the NEET exam, which was held on May 5 but ran into trouble a month later, when results were declared. Such "flip-flops" do not serve students' interests, the court told the agency. "We have highlighted all deficiencies in the structural processes... this we cannot afford for the betterment of the students," the court said Friday morning.

snippet.title: West Bengal Train Accident | What Is TA 912, In Focus After The Kanchanjunga Train Accident?
snippet.description:
The Kanchanjunga Express was travelling from Agartala in Tripura to Sealdah in Kolkata when a goods train hit it from behind near Rangapani station, close to New Jalpaiguri Monday morning, resulting in the deaths of nine people and injuries to 41. Preliminary findings point to a combination of human error and signal failure as contributing factors.

The Railway Board's initial report on Monday revealed that the goods train, operating under a defective automatic signalling system, was travelling above speed limits when it crashed into the Kanchanjunga Express. The railways have not commented on this issue.

When the automated system fails, railway protocol mandates a written authority known as TA 912. This document authorises train drivers to pass all red signals due to the signalling defect, provided they adhere to stringent safety measures. Both the Kanchanjunga Express and the goods train had been issued TA 912.

snippet.title: PM Modi Cabinet News | Pawan Khera Takes Jibe At PM Modi: “Not Modi 3.0, This Is NDA 3.0…”
snippet.description:
Congress leader Pawan Khera took a jibe at Prime Minister Narendra Modi on June 10 over Modi 3.0. He said that this is NDA 3.0 one should ask Chandrababu Naidu and Nitish Kumar if they will call this Modi 3.0 or NDA 3.0?

While speaking to ANI, Congress leader Pawan Khera said, "First of all this is not Modi 3.0, this is NDA 3.0. If you are saying Modi 3.0, you should also ask Chandrababu Naidu and Nitish Kumar if they will call this Modi 3.0 or NDA 3.0? 

PM Modi will understand now that those who used to abuse Nehru, Gandhi family or the Congress party have now been shown the exit gate by the public and now PM Modi is compelled to do the same. Anurag Thakur, the one who used to talk about Hindu-Muslim the most, has only been shown the exit gate..."

snippet.title: Modi 3.0 | PM Modi Starts Term 3, Signs First File "Related To Farmer Welfare"
snippet.description:
Prime Minister Narendra Modi today assumed office for a third consecutive term in his South Block office in Delhi following last evening's swearing-in ceremony, where he led a 72-member Union Council of Ministers into office. The first file that he signed was related to farmers' welfare scheme 'PM Kisan Nidhi'. The immediate agenda for the newly sworn-in Prime Minister includes a Cabinet meeting. The Cabinet is expected to formally request President Droupadi Murmu to summon a session of Parliament. This session will include the President's address to both houses, outlining the government's vision and priorities for the upcoming term.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Exit Poll Numbers | Sonia Gandhi Responds To Exit Polls Ahead Of Counting Day: "Wait And See"
snippet.description:
The INDIA Opposition bloc is hopeful that the results of the 2024 Lok Sabha election will be "completely opposite" to exit poll predictions that have predicted another big victory for the BJP-led NDA, senior Congress leader Sonia Gandhi told news agency PTI.

Asked what are her expectations for tomorrow, the Congress parliamentary party chairperson replied, "We have to wait, just wait and see. We are very hopeful that our results are completely the Opposite of what the exit polls are saying."

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Amit Shah News | "We Will Perform Better Than 2019 In UP": Amit Shah Ahead Of Last Phase Of LS Polls
snippet.description:
The BJP is set to win most Lok Sabha seats in eastern and southern India this time, Union Home Minister Amit Shah has told NDTV in an exclusive interview. Mr Shah was speaking to NDTV's editor-in-chief Sanjay Pugalia on the campaign trail ahead of the last phase of the general election, scheduled to be held this Saturday.

Asked what are his expectations for Odisha, Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, Mr Shah replied, "We will take a significant lead in Bengal too. We may win between 24 and 30 seats (out of 42). In Odisha, our target is 17 Lok Sabha seats (out of 21) and 75 Assembly seats (out of 147). In Telangana, we will win around 10 seats (out of 17). As for Andhra Pradesh, our alliance government is going to form the government and NDA is will win a big chunk of Lok Sabha seats too."

Watch the full interview here: https://youtube.com/live/BWxhQFbCGtI

snippet.title: Amit Shah News | "BJP Will Win 17 Lok Sabha And 75 Assembly Seats In Odisha": Amit Shah to NDTV
snippet.description:
The BJP is set to win most Lok Sabha seats in eastern and southern India this time, Union Home Minister Amit Shah has told NDTV in an exclusive interview. Mr Shah was speaking to NDTV's editor-in-chief Sanjay Pugalia on the campaign trail ahead of the last phase of the general election, scheduled to be held this Saturday.

Asked what are his expectations for Odisha, Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, Mr Shah replied, "We will take a significant lead in Bengal too. We may win between 24 and 30 seats (out of 42). In Odisha, our target is 17 Lok Sabha seats (out of 21) and 75 Assembly seats (out of 147). In Telangana, we will win around 10 seats (out of 17). As for Andhra Pradesh, our alliance government is going to form the government and NDA is will win a big chunk of Lok Sabha seats too."

snippet.title: Manipur Floods Latest | Manipur Minister Drives Bulldozer, Clears Choked River Amid Floods
snippet.description:
The water level in Nambul River in the heart of Manipur’s capital Imphal suddenly rose and breached the riverbank in many areas on May 30, after heavy rain brought by Cyclone Remal battered the state. The valley areas had not completed rebuilding many homes damaged by a strong hailstorm in early May. The floods added to the hardships, with thousands of people displaced by the Meitei-Kuki ethnic clashes still living in relief camps. In mobile videos taken by residents involved in relief work, Manipur’s Public Health Engineering Minister Leishangthem Susindro was seen driving a huge bulldozer towards the Nambul riverbank.

snippet.description:

localized.title: Payal Kapadia | Why FTII Was Criticised For Celebrating Historic Cannes Win
localized.description:
All We Imagine As Light: Director Payal Kapadia’s groundbreaking Grand Prix win at Cannes 2024 for her debut feature film, All We Imagine As Light, a recognition that India has been bestowed after 30 years, has taken social media by storm. However, many on social media haven't taken kindly to her alma mater FTII congratulating her on the big win. While several from the film industry are congratulating Payal on her huge achievement, a congratulatory message from her alma mater, the Film and Television Institute of India (FTII), which once took disciplinary action against her, has received flak from many on social media, who accused the institute of having "double standards"

snippet.title: Payal Kapadia's 'All We Imagine As Light' Wins Grand Prix Award At Cannes | NDTV World
snippet.description:
Indian filmmaker Payal Kapadia scripted history as her spellbinding drama "All We Imagine as Light" won the Grand Prix award at the 77th Cannes Film Festival. The Grand Prix Award is the second most prestigious award at festival after the Palme d'Or, and was awarded to Kapadia after her film received an eight-minute standing ovation at its world premiere. 

Kapadia's feature directorial debut, which screened on Thursday night has received glowing reviews in the international press, and has already registered its name in the history books after becoming the first Indian film in 30 years and the first ever by an Indian female director to be showcased in the main competition.

snippet.title: PM Modi Interview | PM's Message To Youth Of India: "Connect With Elders In Family"
snippet.description:
In an exclusive interview to NDTV, Prime Minister Narendra Modi gave a message to the youth of India. The Prime Minister shared that during COVID-19, he requested the youth to connect with the elderly in the family. Speaking to NDTV Editor-in-Chief Sanjay Pugalia, the Prime Minister said, "During Covid, I used to do video conferencing and requested the youth to interview their grandparents and ask them how life was when they were young. How things were in school when they used to study, how weddings used to take place during their times, how relatives used to live in small houses." The Prime Minister said this would help them connect with the elders of the house and understand their lives and how they worked hard to reach this stage. 

Watch the full interview here: https://youtu.be/pj6G3m_hIlI

Nexus that kills citizens can only be dubbed as criminal. The Mumbai hoarding collapse on May 13 that left 17 people dead and over 70 injured is a living example. NDTV has accessed the 3299-page chargesheet in the Ghatkopar Hoarding collapse case. Tune in to the full show Last Word on NDTV.

#MumbaiBillboardCollapse #MumbaiStormTragedy #DustStorm #Hoarding #Mumbai #MumbaiHoardingChargesheet
